sentences: Deitra Farr (born August 1, 1957) is an American blues, soul and gospel singer-songwriter.
From 1993 to 1996, she was the lead singer for Mississippi Heat and recorded two albums with them, Learned the Hard Way and Thunder in my Heart.
In 1997, she released her first solo album titled The Search is Over, on the British record label, JSP Records.
In 2005, Farr released her second JSP album, Let It Go.
Since 1990, she has toured internationally, so far performing in over 30 countries.
In October 2015, Farr was inducted into the Chicago Blues Hall of Fame as a "Legendary Blues Artist".
Deitra received  " The Koko Taylor Queen of the Blues Award" from the Jus Blues Music Foundation on August 3, 2017.
